"""_0_types.py"""

'''
Assignment Operators:
======================

| ------------ | ---------------------| ----------------------------------------| -----------------| ---------------------- | --------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Operator     | Name                 | Purpose (Simple Meaning)                | Math Analogy     | Python Example         | Output          | Real-World Use Case                                             |
| ------------ | ---------------------| ----------------------------------------| ---------------- | ---------------------- | --------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| =            | Assign               | Stores a value into a variable          | x = 5            | x = 10                 | 10              | Store user input, configs, loading initial values               |
| +=           | Add & Assign         | Adds right value and stores back        | x = x + 10       | x = x + 10 → x += 10   | Updated value   | Billing increments, score update, cumulative sums               |
| -=           | Subtract & Assign    | Subtracts right value and stores back   | x = x - 2        | x = x - 5 → x -= 5     | Updated value   | Inventory deduction, countdown timers                           |
| *=           | Multiply & Assign    | Multiplies and stores back              | x = x * 2        | x = x * 4 → x *= 4     | Updated value   | Scaling factors, quantity multipliers                           |
| /=           | Divide & Assign      | Divides and stores back (float result)  | x = x / 2        | x = x / 3 → x /= 3     | Updated value   | Average calculations, rate conversions                          |
| //=          | Floor Divide & Assign| Floor divides and stores back           | x = floor(x/2)   | x = x // 3 → x //= 3   | Updated value   | Chunking data, pagination, batch processing                     |
| %=           | Modulus & Assign     | Finds remainder and stores back         | x = x % n        | x = x % 7 → x %= 7     | Updated value   | Cyclic counters, rotations, periodic events                     |
| **=          | Power & Assign       | Raises to power and stores back         | x = xⁿ           | x = x ** 3 → x **= 3   | Updated value   | Growth models, compounding interest, math algorithms            |
| &=           | Bitwise AND & Assign | Bitwise AND operation and store back    | x = x AND y      | x = x & y → x &= y     | Updated value   | Permission flags, masking bits                                  |
| |=           | Bitwise OR & Assign  | Bitwise OR and store back               | x = x OR y       | x = x | y → x |= y     | Updated value   | Feature toggles, combining flags                                |
| ^=           | Bitwise XOR & Assign | Bitwise XOR and store back              | x = x XOR y      | x = x ^ y → x ^= y     | Updated value   | Encryption logic, bit-level diff detection                      |
| <<=          | Left Shift & Assign  | Shifts bits to the left and stores back | x = x × 2ⁿ       | x = x << 2 → x <<= 2   | Updated value   | Fast multiplication, buffer movement, encoding                  |
| >>=          | Right Shift & Assign | Shifts bits to the right and stores back| x = x ÷ 2ⁿ       | x = x >> 1 → x >>= 1   | Updated value   | Fast division, compression, trimming bits                       |
| ------------ | ---------------------| ----------------------------------------| ---------------- | ---------------------- | --------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |

'''